OL,3,CHorizon scandal victims who never saw
OL,4,Cjustice before death
OL,6,FJustice came too late for Sue Beacock
OL,7,Fas well. She bought a post office in
OL,8,FDorset with her mother, Kathleen - who
OL,9,Fwas herself an experienced
OL,10,Fsubpostmistress.
OL,12,FNine years later, Sue was wrongfully
OL,13,Fdismissed for false accounting.
OL,14,FKathleen died thinking her daughter
OL,15,Fwas a thief.
OL,17,F"I can never tell her that it wasn't
OL,18,Fme - it was the system," Sue weeps.
OL,19,F"She will never know."
