OL,4,Cjustice before death
OL,6,FPeople who take over the running of
OL,7,Ftheir local post office tend to have a
OL,8,Fsense of community.
OL,10,FSitting at their counters, they were
OL,11,Fthe face of what for many of their
OL,12,Fneighbours was a vital public service.
OL,14,FIt is little wonder that after being
OL,15,Ffound guilty of abusing their
OL,16,Fpositions of trust - they were
OL,17,Fconsumed by the shame.
